   Special Interest Grp Comp Graph},
Abstract = {Nowadays, novice users often turn to digital tutorials for guidance in
   software. However, searching and utilizing the tutorial remains a
   challenge due to the request for proper problem articulation, extensive
   searches and mind-intensive follow-through. We introduce ``Docent{''}, a
   system designed to bridge this knowledge-seeking gap. Powered by Large
   Language Models (LLMs), Docent takes vague user input and recent digital
   operation contexts to reason, seek, and present the most relevant
   tutorials in-situ. We assume that Docent smooths the user experience and
   facilitates learning of the software.},
