   Liapis, Antonios},
Book-Group-Author = {IEEE},
Title = {PyPLT: Python Preference Learning Toolbox},
Booktitle = {2019 8TH INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON AFFECTIVE COMPUTING AND INTELLIGENT
   INTERACTION (ACII)},
Series = {International Conference on Affective Computing and Intelligent
   Interaction},
Year = {2019},
Note = {8th International Conference on Affective Computing and Intelligent
   Interaction (ACII), Cambridge, ENGLAND, SEP 03-06, 2019},
Abstract = {There is growing evidence suggesting that subjective values such as
   emotions are intrinsically relative and that an ordinal approach is
   beneficial to their annotation and analysis. Ordinal data processing
   yields more reliable, valid and general predictive models, and
   preference learning algorithms have shown a strong advantage in deriving
   computational models from such data. To enable the extensive use of
   ordinal data processing and preference learning, this paper introduces
   the Python Preference Learning Toolbox. The toolbox is open source,
   features popular preference learning algorithms and methods, and is
   designed to be accessible to a wide audience of researchers and
   practitioners. The toolbox is evaluated with regards to both the
   accuracy of its predictive models across two affective datasets and its
   usability via a user study. Our key findings suggest that the
   implemented algorithms yield accurate models of affect while its
   graphical user interface is suitable for both novice and experienced
   users.},
